# Loctran — cursor rules

## Project identity
- Package: loctran (v0.1.1b1, Python ≥ 3.9)
- Purpose: local AI PDF translator — no cloud calls, no API keys
- License: Apache 2.0

## Layout
loctran/
  cli.py            # Click entry points (loctran translate, loctran doctor)
  extract.py        # OCR + segmentation (Tesseract, pdfplumber, pypdfium2)
  translate.py      # LLM translation + HTML overlay (Ollama)
  diagnostics.py    # Health checks (loctran doctor)
  server/
    server.py       # FastAPI app + job orchestration
    compress.py     # PDF / image compression
    store.py        # SQLite job persistence
tests/              # pytest (≥70 % coverage gate)

## Style rules (enforced by ruff — do not contradict)
- Line length: 88
- Formatter: ruff format (not black)
- Import order: ruff (isort-compatible), stdlib → third-party → local
- Type hints: required on all public functions (from __future__ import annotations)
- Docstrings: Google style, one-line summary then blank line then body if needed
- No commented-out code
- No bare except: — always name the exception

## Naming
- Functions: snake_case verbs  (extract_segments, run_pipeline)
- Classes: PascalCase nouns    (JobDict, CompressResult)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE   (DEFAULT_MODEL, JOB_RETENTION_SECONDS)
- Private helpers: leading _   (_start_ollama_if_needed)
- No abbreviations except: src, dst, pdf, ocr, llm, html, url, db

## External dependencies
- Never import from app.* or translate.* at module level in extract.py (circular)
- ollama, pytesseract, pdfplumber, pypdfium2 are always available in runtime env
- rich is available; use it for any terminal output (no bare print in non-test code)
- Never add new dependencies without updating pyproject.toml AND requirements comment

## Testing
- Mock Ollama calls with unittest.mock.patch("ollama.chat")
- Mock Tesseract calls with unittest.mock.patch("pytesseract.image_to_data")
- Use pytest tmp_path for any file I/O
- Do not write to the real uploads/ or outputs/ directories in tests

## Forbidden patterns
- pkill, killall, os.system — use subprocess.Popen with explicit PID tracking
- shutil.rmtree without confirming path is inside tmp_path or the loctran data dir
- print() outside of tests or __main__ blocks — use rich.console or logging
- Hardcoded paths like /home/user or C:\Users — always use pathlib.Path.home()
- String formatting with % — use f-strings

## Git
- Commit style: conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:, test:, refactor:)
- Branch style: feat/short-description, fix/short-description
- Never commit uploads/, outputs/, dist/, *.egg-info/, __pycache__/
